##CodeOlympics  
###Time Limit : 2 hours

## Questions
* The prime factors of 73825 are 5 ,5 , 2953. Largest prime factor of this number is 2953

What is the largest prime factor of the number 9809914751476 ?

* Indian currency is made up of ₹ (Rupees ) and paise  of following kinds:
	 50p, 100p,  1 ₹ , 2 ₹ , 5₹ , 10 ₹ 50 ₹ , 100 ₹ , 500₹ and 1000₹
	It is possible to make 20000 ₹ in the following way:
	 2 x 50 p + 9 x 100p + 1000x19 ₹ + 500 x 1 ₹ + 4 x 100 ₹ + 10 x 9 ₹
How many different ways can 20000 ₹  be made using any number of coins?

* The sum of the primes below 15 is 2 + 3 + 5 + 7 + 11 + 13 =  41.
Find the sum of all the primes below three million.

* n! means n × (n − 1) × ... × 3 × 2 × 1
For example, 14! = 14 x 13 X …10 × 9 × ... × 3 × 2 × 1 = 87178291200,
and the sum of the digits in the number 14! is 8+ 7+1+7+8+2+9+1+2 +0 + 0 = 45. Find the sum of the digits in the number 113!
